@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{read-aloud-extras.el} extends the @samp{read-aloud} package, which provides text-to-speech functionality within Emacs. The base package handles the core reading pipeline, but it offers limited control over speech parameters and does not support PDF buffers. This package fills those gaps with:

@itemize
@item
User options and commands for adjusting the speech rate on the fly (@ref{Rate options}, @ref{Rate commands}).
@item
A user option and command for choosing the speech voice (@ref{Voice option}, @ref{Setting the voice}).
@item
A command to read entire files, including PDFs, by extracting their text first (@ref{Reading files}).
@item
A patch via @samp{el-patch} that enables reading selected text in @samp{pdf-view-mode} buffers (@ref{PDF selection patch}).
@end itemize

The speech-engine customization is currently implemented for the macOS @samp{say} backend. The package depends on @samp{el-patch} and @samp{read-aloud}.

