@node Rate options
@section Rate options

@vindex read-aloud-extras-rate
The user option @code{read-aloud-extras-rate} specifies the speech rate in words per minute. The default value is @samp{200}, which corresponds to a natural conversational pace. You can change this to any integer; higher values produce faster speech. This value is passed to the speech engine whenever the engine configuration is updated (@ref{Rate commands}).

@vindex read-aloud-extras-rate-change
The user option @code{read-aloud-extras-rate-change} controls the increment or decrement applied by the @code{read-aloud-extras-increase-rate} and @code{read-aloud-extras-decrease-rate} commands. The default value is @samp{10} words per minute. If you find the adjustments too coarse or too fine, change this value accordingly.

@node Voice option
@section Voice option

@vindex read-aloud-extras-voice
The user option @code{read-aloud-extras-voice} holds the name of the voice used by the speech engine. It is a string that must match a voice recognized by the configured engine (for macOS @samp{say}, examples include @samp{"Alex"}, @samp{"Samantha"}, @samp{"Daniel"}). The default is an empty string, which causes the engine to use its own default voice. Change this option or use the @code{read-aloud-extras-set-voice} command (@ref{Setting the voice}) to select a specific voice.

