@node Engine configuration
@section Engine configuration

@findex read-aloud-extras-update-engine
@findex read-aloud-extras-update-current-engine
@findex read-aloud-extras-update-say-engine
The function @code{read-aloud-extras-update-engine} updates the parameters for a named engine in the @code{read-aloud-engines} variable. The function @code{read-aloud-extras-update-current-engine} dispatches to the appropriate engine-specific updater based on the value of @code{read-aloud-engine}; currently only the @samp{say} engine is supported. The function @code{read-aloud-extras-update-say-engine} constructs the argument list for the macOS @samp{say} command using the current values of @code{read-aloud-extras-voice} and @code{read-aloud-extras-rate}.

These functions are called automatically by the rate and voice commands (@ref{Rate commands}, @ref{Setting the voice}) and do not normally need to be invoked directly.

@node Voice selection
@section Voice selection

@findex read-aloud-extras-select-say-voice
The function @code{read-aloud-extras-select-say-voice} queries the system for available @samp{say} voices by running @samp{say -v \?}, parses the output into a list of voice-name and language pairs, and prompts the user with @code{completing-read}. It returns the selected voice name as a string. This function is called by @code{read-aloud-extras-set-voice} (@ref{Setting the voice}).

